reviewText: What I love about Melrose is that anything can happen...anytime!  The twists and turns, particularly the ending is amazing!  What a phenomenal series!

Well, this last instalment of season 7 was fantastic! I wished each season was released in one boxset... but I was keen to watch the show asap so I purchased all the half seasons and with almost 18 - 20 episodes per half season you can understand why they did it this way.
These dvd's saw so much dramas as relationships were 'finalised', death, drama and babies formulated this final episodes. I remember watching these final days of Melrose on tv and everyone was predicting how it would all come to an end... great to relieve these moments.... you won't be disappointed :)

This was one of the classic TV shows that I had to own.  It is nice to see the gang back as I take a stroll down memory lane. Melrose Place Final season volume 2 is the count down to the end. There are a lot of laughs and even a few tears. The story lines crumble around Eve but the whole overall feeling is a quirky fun melrose we all know and love. The whole cast delivers knock out performances till the very end. This season had a lot of ups and downs but volume to is really a fun kind of ending because it delivers so many laugh out loud moments. Though some points of this volume are slow, the story still keeps your grasp wanting to see what happens next. A must buy for true Melrose fans!

This 1998-99 Season of MELROSE PLACE was awesome, despite the fact that it wasn't as successful as its predecessor BEVERLY HILLS 90210, plus I liked the return of Jane Mancini  (Josie Bissett) whom was married to co-star Rob Estes  (Kyle McBride) at the time.

Love Melrose Place, all the drama, lies, bitch-slapping, blackmail, cheating, and betrayal you'd expect. I'm so glad they put the entire series on DVD. I miss the 90s because today we are flooded with reality TV no good scripted dramas like these from the late Aaron Spelling.
